SIMPLE: insoluble
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Insoluble
<hw>In*sol"u*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>insolubilis</ets> indissoluble, that can not be loosed: cf. F.
<ets>insoluble</ets>. See <er>In-</er> not, and <er>Soluble</er>, and
cf. <er>Insolvable</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Not soluble; in capable or difficult of being
dissolved, as by a liquid; <as>as, chalk is <ex>insoluble</ex> in
water</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not to be solved or explained; insolvable; <as>as,
an <ex>insoluble</ex> doubt, question, or difficulty</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Strong.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧An <xex>insoluble</xex>
wall.⟦rdquo⟧ <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Holland</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insolubleness</ent>⟦br⟧
